This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on visual recognition networks and improving their performance. It also involves object detection, which is a common task in computer vision. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as learning the neuron allocation, which suggests it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The use of deep networks and convolutional operations suggests that the paper could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The paper's focus on multi-scale representations and information fusion suggests it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper's use of ImageNet classification and COCO object detection suggests it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
